; NAME: Get Helpful Item (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -48 ; Including 4 byte pad
SW RA 40(SP)
SW S2 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)
SW S0 28(SP)

; BEGIN SHOW WELCOME MESSAGE CODE
; This code block displays a message specified below under
; "welcomeMsg".
; You can remove this block if you want, but remember
; to remove the welcomeMsg block as well, including "align 16".

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(welcomeMsg)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(welcomeMsg)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; END SHOW WELCOME MESSAGE CODE

; BEGIN DETERMINE PLAYER CODE
; This code block makes sure that the current player is the one
; getting the item. Written by PartyPlanner64.

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP

ADDU S0 R0 R0

LUI S1 hi(p1_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p2_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p2_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p3_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p3_item1)

BEQ S0 V0 determineslot
NOP
ADDIU S0 S0 1

LUI S1 hi(p4_item1)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p4_item1)

; END DETERMINE PLAYER CODE

; BEGIN ANALYZE INVENTORY CODE
; This code block checks if the current player can fit the item.
; If not, we proceed to the next block. Otherwise, we jump ahead
; to "giveitem".

determineslot:
ADDIU S2 R0 0xFF
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitem ; First slot empty (0xFF)
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitem
NOP
ADDIU S1 S1 1
LBU S0 0(S1)
BEQ S0 S2 giveitem
NOP

; END ANALYZE INVENTORY CODE

; BEGIN SHOW "CANNOT GIVE ITEM" MESSAGE CODE
; This code block displays a message specified below under
; "cannotGiveItemMsg", if the current player has a full invetory.
; You can remove this block if you want, but remember
; to remove the cannotGiveItemMsg block as well, including "align 16".

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
LUI A1 hi(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(cannotGiveItemMsg)
ADDU A2 R0 R0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; END SHOW "CANNOT GIVE ITEM" MESSAGE CODE

J exit
NOP

giveitem:

;BEGIN DETERMINE ITEM CODE

; This code block generates a random 8-bit integer (0-255) and
; iteratively checks how big it is. Depending on its size, one of
; five different items can be received. By changing the size and 
; number of the intervals, any number of items can be included in the 
; list with separate and specific odds of getting them.

JAL 0x8000B16C ; Generates an integer.
NOP

ADDIU A0 R0 0x34 ; Is the number less than 52? (20% chance)
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BNE S0 R0 getitemone ; If so, get item one.
NOP

; If we got here, it is not less than 52.

ADDIU A0 R0 0x67 ; Is it less than 103? (40% chance)
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BNE S0 R0 getitemtwo ; If so, get item two.
NOP

; If we got here, it is not less than 103.

ADDIU A0 R0 0x9A ; Is it less than 154? (60% chance)
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BNE S0 R0 getitemthree ; If so, get item three.
NOP

; If we got here, it is not less than 154.

ADDIU A0 R0 0xCD ; Is it less than 205? (80% chance)
SLT S0 V0 A0
NOP

BNE S0 R0 getitemfour ; If so, get item four.
NOP

; If we got here, it is not less than 205. Since we have a 20% chance
; of reaching this point, let's just get item five.

J getitemfive
NOP

; END DETERMINE ITEM CODE

; BEGIN GET ITEM CODE
; This code block gives the player one of the items chosen in
; the previous block. The item values can be changed to any value
; in this table:
; 0x00 = Mushroom
; 0x01 = Skeleton Key
; 0x02 = Poison Mushroom
; 0x03 = Reverse Mushroom
; 0x04 = Cellular Shopper
; 0x05 = Warp Block
; 0x06 = Plunder Chest
; 0x07 = Bowser Phone
; 0x08 = Dueling Glove
; 0x09 = Lucky Lamp
; 0x0A = Golden Mushroom
; 0x0B = Boo Bell
; 0x0C = Boo Repellant
; 0x0D = Bowser Suit
; 0x0E = Magic Lamp
; 0x0F = Koopa Card
; 0x10 = Barter Box
; 0x11 = Lucky Coin
; 0x12 = Wacky Watch

getitemone:
ADDIU S2 R0 0x03 ; Skeleton Key value
SB S2 0(S1)
J bye
getitemtwo:
ADDIU S2 R0 0x03 ; Skeleton Key value
SB S2 0(S1)
J bye
getitemthree:
ADDIU S2 R0 0x05 ; Skeleton Key value
SB S2 0(S1)
J bye
getitemfour:
ADDIU S2 R0 0x05 ; Skeleton Key value
SB S2 0(S1)
J bye
getitemfive:
ADDIU S2 R0 0x0B ; Skeleton Key value
SB S2 0(S1)

; END GET ITEM CODE

bye:

; BEGIN BYE MESSAGE CODE
; This code block displays a bye message specified below under
; "byeMsg". You can remove this block if you want, but remember
; to remove the byeMsg block as well, including "align 16".

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4

ADDIU A1 A1 lo(byeMsg)

ADDU A3 R0 R0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; END BYE MESSAGE CODE

LW S0 28(SP)

Big Boo Warp (Boardwalk).code:
; NAME: Big Boo Warp (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 16 ; Fade Out for 16 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 16 ; Sleep 16 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)
;WARP END------------------------------------------------------------

;SOUND START---------------------------------------------------------
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 15 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 15 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish
;SOUND END-----------------------------------------------------------

;FADE-IN START-------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames of Fade-in

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 31 ; Sleep for 31 Frames
;FADE-IN END---------------------------------------------------------

;MESSAGE DISPLAY START-----------------------------------------------
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0x0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL CloseMessage
NOP
;MESSAGE DISPLAY END-------------------------------------------------



LW RA 76(SP)
LW S4 72(SP)
LW S5 68(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; .ascii is used to output Text. Anything surrounded by " will be 
; displayed in the message (Special characters are not included).
; For those, you must use .byte and the respective byte value.
; Bytes that change text color will change the color of everything
; that is written after it, until another color is used.

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "You were warped to a"
.byte 0x0A ;
.ascii "different space by Big Boo"
.byte 0xC2 ; 
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
; .byte 0x5C ; Apostrophe (')
; .byte 0x29 ; Coin icon
; .byte 0x3D ; - (minus)
; .byte 0x3E ; x (multiply)
; .byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

; If your message has an image, use this at the start of each line
; .byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Padding for picture

.align 4
PlaySadVoice:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP 

LUI T1 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Character address
MULT V0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by T0
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to T0

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's Character address
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into T0

ADDIU V0 T0 0x287 ; Mario's Sad Voice Index

JAL PlaySound
MOVE A0 V0 ; Pass the Voice Index to A0

LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

Boo Toll v1.1 (Boardwalk).code:
; NAME: Boo Toll v1.1 (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|DeclineDestination
; PARAM: Space|DeclineInReverse
; PARAM: +Number|StartingToll

ADDIU SP SP -72
SW RA 64(SP)
SW S0 60(SP)
SW S1 56(SP)
SW S2 52(SP)
SW S3 48(SP)
SW S4 44(SP)
SW S6 40(SP)
SW S7 36(SP)

; S1 = Player Status Flag Address
; S3 = Toll Address
; S2 = Toll Address value
; S4 = Current Player's Index
; S6 = Base Toll
; S7 = Current Player's Coin Amount
; DeclineDestination = Where the player would go if they say no/don't
;                      have enough coins
; DeclineInReverse = Where the player would go if they say no/don't
;                    have enough coins, but they are going in reverse
; StartingToll = What the Thwomp Toll will start at

LI A0 -1
LI A1 -1
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; At V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0

LUI S3 hi(0x800CD0A4)
ADDIU S3 S3 lo(0x800CD0A4) ; Load Address of Board-Specific RAM
LHU S2 0(S3) ; Load the RAM Value into S1

LUI A0 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coin_string_loc)
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d)
MOVE A2 S2 ; Move Thwomp Toll Total Value into A2
JAL sprintf
NOP

BNE S2 R0 Check
NOP

LI S2 StartingToll ; Set Starting Toll if address reads 0

;FAILSAFE CHECK======================================================
Check:
MOVE A0 S4
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; Checks if Player has the minimum coin amount
MOVE A1 S2

BEQ V0 R0 NotEnoughCoins
NOP
;FAILSAFE CHECK======================================================
MOVE S6 S2 ; Copy Base Toll to S6

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Thwomp's cry

LUI T1 hi(p1_coins)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_coins) ; Load Player 1's Coins
LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's coins address
MULT S4 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's coins address
LHU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into S2
MOVE S7 T0 ; Move Value into S7

START:
LUI A0 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coin_string_loc)
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d)
MOVE A2 S2 ; Move Thwomp Toll Total Value into A2
JAL sprintf
NOP

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Thwomp)
LUI A1 hi(Thwomp_Prompt)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Thwomp_Prompt)
LUI A2 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A2 A2 lo(coin_string_loc) ; Pass ThwompToll as String
LI A3 0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
NOP

; If A0 is a pointer to AI data, AI logic is ran to pick for CPUs.
; If A0 is 0 or 1, the 0th or 1st option is chosen by CPUs.
; If A0 is 2, then the value of A1 is the CPUs option index choice.
LUI A0 hi(ai_random_choice)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(ai_random_choice)
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
LI A1 0
MOVE S0 V0 ; S0 now has the chosen option index

; Obligatory message box closing/cleanup calls.
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

; Change the outcome based on the choice.
LI A0 0
BEQ S0 A0 yes
NOP
LI A0 1
BEQ S0 A0 no
NOP
LI A0 2
BEQ S0 A0 viewmap
NOP


yes:
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Thwomp)
LUI A1 hi(ThwompToll_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ThwompToll_Message)
LUI A2 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A2 A2 lo(coin_string_loc) ; Pass ThwompToll as String
LI A3 0
JAL 0x800EC92C  ; ShowMessage2
NOP

JAL PlayerIsCPU ; Returns 1 if the current player is a CPU
MOVE A0 S4

BNE V0 R0 exitloop
NOP

LoopReturn:
MOVE A0 S4
JAL DetectCStickInput ; V0 = 1 if Stick is Up, -1 if Down, ELSE 0
NOP

BEQ V0 R0 Loop
NOP

LI T0 1
BEQ V0 T0 CheckMax
NOP
J CheckMin
NOP

CheckMax:
BNE S2 S7 ContinueNormal
NOP
MOVE S2 S6
J ContinueRefresh
NOP

CheckMin:
BNE S2 S6 ContinueNormal
NOP
MOVE S2 S7
J ContinueRefresh
NOP

ContinueNormal:
ADDU S2 S2 V0

ContinueRefresh:
LUI A0 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coin_string_loc)
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d)
MOVE A2 S2 ; Move Thwomp Toll Total Value into A2
JAL sprintf
NOP

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 582 ; Coin Sound

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 2 ; Sleep for 2 frames so choosing amount is easier

Loop:
MOVE A0 S4
JAL DetectABInput ; V0 = 1 if A press, 2 if B press, ELSE 0
NOP

LI T0 1
BEQ V0 T0 exitloop
NOP
BEQ V0 R0 ContinueInLoop
NOP

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 4 ; Back Sound Index

JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP
MOVE S2 S6
J START
NOP

ContinueInLoop:
LI A0 2
LUI A1 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(coin_string_loc)
JAL 0x8005B6BC
MOVE A2 R0

LI A0 2
LUI A1 hi(ThwompToll_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ThwompToll_Message)
LI A2 -1
JAL 0x8005B43C
LI A3 -1

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

J LoopReturn
NOP



exitloop:
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 583 ; Cash Register Sound

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 10 ; Sleep 10 frames

MOVE A0 S4
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
SUBU A1 R0 S2

MOVE A0 S4
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
SUBU A1 R0 S2

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Sleep 30 frames

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Thwomp's cry

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Thwomp)
LUI A1 hi(ThwompYes_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ThwompYes_Message)
LI A2 0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

ADDIU S2 S2 1 ; Add 1 to the toll count
SH S2 0(S3) ; Update the minimum amount of Coins for the Toll

J exit
NOP


no:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Thwomp's cry

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Thwomp)
LUI A1 hi(ThwompNo_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ThwompNo_Message)
LI A2 0
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

StatusFlag:
LUI S1 hi(p1_status_flags)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_status_flags) ; Load Player 1's Status Flag
LI T0 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Flag
MULT S4 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU S1 S1 T0 ; Add result to get Current Player Status Flag Address

LBU A1 0(S1) ; Load address value into A1
LI A0 7
JAL GetPlayerBit ; V0 = 1 if Reversed
NOP

BNE V0 R0 PlayerInReverse ; If it's not 0, they're in Reverse
NOP

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 DeclineDestination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
LI A2 DeclineDestination_chain_space_index ;Assigns Space Index to A2
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
NOP

J exit
NOP

PlayerInReverse:
MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 DeclineInReverse_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
LI A2 DeclineInReverse_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
NOP

LBU T0 0(S1)
ADDIU T0 T0 1
SB T0 0(S1)

J exit
NOP

viewmap:
JAL ViewBoardMap
NOP
J START
NOP


NotEnoughCoins:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Thwomp's cry

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Thwomp)
LUI A1 hi(ThwompNotEnoughCoins_Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ThwompNotEnoughCoins_Message)
LUI A2 hi(coin_string_loc)
ADDIU A2 A2 lo(coin_string_loc)
JAL 0x800EC8EC ; ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6C8
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

J StatusFlag
NOP


exit:
LW RA 64(SP)
LW S0 60(SP)
LW S1 56(SP)
LW S2 52(SP)
LW S3 48(SP)
LW S4 44(SP)
LW S6 40(SP)
LW S7 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 72

; Gets player A0's bit value
; A0 = bit to shift to (7)
; A1 = player flag address value
GetPlayerBit:
ADDIU SP SP -8
SW RA 0(SP)

LI T0 1
SLLV T0 T0 A0 ; shift bit mask into position

AND T2 A1 T0

BEQ T2 R0 ret_zero
NOP

ret_one:
LI V0 1
J getplayerbit_exit
NOP

ret_zero:
LI V0 0

getplayerbit_exit:
LW RA 0(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 8


; A0 Current Player index
DetectCStickInput:
ADDIU SP SP -20
SW RA 16(SP)
SW S5 12(SP)

LUI T1 hi(p1_controller)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_controller) ; Load P1's Controller
LI T0 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Controller
MULT A0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get Current Player's Controller Addr
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into A1

LUI T1 hi(0x800CC3F7)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(0x800CC3F7) ; Load P1's Y Axis
LI A2 0x8 ; This is the distance between each player's Controller
MULT A2 T0 ;  Multiply Controller value by 8
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get Current Player's Y Axis
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into A1

SLTI S5 T0 0x1E ; S5 = 1 if less than 1E
NOP
BNE S5 R0 return_zero 
NOP
SLTI S5 T0 0x7C ; Set if Stick is tilted up
NOP
BNE S5 R0 return_one
NOP
SLTI S5 T0 0xE2
NOP
BNE S5 R0 return_neg_one
NOP

return_zero:
LI V0 0
J DetectCStickInputexit
NOP

return_one:
LI V0 1
J DetectCStickInputexit
NOP

return_neg_one:
LI V0 -1
J DetectCStickInputexit
NOP

DetectCStickInputexit:
LW RA 16(SP)
LW S5 12(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 20

; A0 Current Player's Control Stick Y axis
DetectABInput:
ADDIU SP SP -20
SW RA 16(SP)

LUI T1 hi(p1_controller)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_controller) ; Load P1's Controller
LI T0 0x38 ; This is the distance between each player's Controller
MULT A0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by S3
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get Current Player's Controller Addr
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into A1

LUI T1 hi(0x800CCF7C)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(0x800CCF7C) ; Load P1's Button Press Address
LI A2 0x2 ; This is the distance between each player's Button Address
MULT A2 T0 ;  Multiply Controller value by 2
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to S3

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get Current Player's Y Axis
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into A1

LI T1 0x80
BEQ T0 T1 APress
NOP
LI T1 0x40
BEQ T0 T1 BPress
NOP

NoPress:
LI V0 0
J DetectABInputexit
NOP

APress:
LI V0 1
J DetectABInputexit
NOP

BPress:
LI V0 2
J DetectABInputexit
NOP

DetectABInputexit:
LW RA 16(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 20



.align 4
percent_d:
.asciiz "%d" ; 0x25640000

coin_string_loc:
.fill 8

.align 16
ai_random_choice:
.word 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x064C9932

.align 16
ThwompNotEnoughCoins_Message:
.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture
.ascii "Not enough coins"
.byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
.ascii " Forget it"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture
.ascii "Youre going in the hole"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

.align 16
Thwomp_Prompt:

.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture
.ascii "Boy oh boy"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.ascii " It appears"
.byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture
.ascii "I am the last thing standing"
.byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture
.ascii "between you and the black hole"
.byte 0x85 ;
.byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
.byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Standard padding for picture

Bargain Boo Good Warp (Boardwalk).code:
; NAME: Bargain Boo Good Warp (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 16 ; Fade Out for 16 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 16 ; Sleep 16 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)
;WARP END------------------------------------------------------------

;SOUND START---------------------------------------------------------
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 15 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x107 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 15 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish
;SOUND END-----------------------------------------------------------

;FADE-IN START-------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames of Fade-in

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 31 ; Sleep for 31 Frames
;FADE-IN END---------------------------------------------------------

;MESSAGE DISPLAY START-----------------------------------------------
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0x0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL CloseMessage
NOP
;MESSAGE DISPLAY END-------------------------------------------------



LW RA 76(SP)
LW S4 72(SP)
LW S5 68(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; .ascii is used to output Text. Anything surrounded by " will be 
; displayed in the message (Special characters are not included).
; For those, you must use .byte and the respective byte value.
; Bytes that change text color will change the color of everything
; that is written after it, until another color is used.

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "You were warped back to"
.byte 0x0A ;
.ascii "the beginning by Bargain Boo"
.byte 0xC2 ; 
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
; .byte 0x5C ; Apostrophe (')
; .byte 0x29 ; Coin icon
; .byte 0x3D ; - (minus)
; .byte 0x3E ; x (multiply)
; .byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

; If your message has an image, use this at the start of each line
; .byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Padding for picture

.align 4
PlaySadVoice:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP 

LUI T1 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Character address
MULT V0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by T0
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to T0

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's Character address
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into T0

ADDIU V0 T0 0x287 ; Mario's Sad Voice Index

JAL PlaySound
MOVE A0 V0 ; Pass the Voice Index to A0

LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

Big Boo Spit Up Warp (Boardwalk).code:
; NAME: Big Boo Spit Up Warp (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 12 ; Fade Out for 12 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 16 ; Sleep 16 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)
;WARP END------------------------------------------------------------

;SOUND START---------------------------------------------------------
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr
JAL PlaySound ; Play Blowing Away Sound
LI A0 0x190

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 15 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish
;SOUND END-----------------------------------------------------------

;FADE-IN START-------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames of Fade-in

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 31 ; Sleep for 31 Frames
;FADE-IN END---------------------------------------------------------

;MESSAGE DISPLAY START-----------------------------------------------
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0x0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL CloseMessage
NOP
;MESSAGE DISPLAY END-------------------------------------------------



LW RA 76(SP)
LW S4 72(SP)
LW S5 68(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; .ascii is used to output Text. Anything surrounded by " will be 
; displayed in the message (Special characters are not included).
; For those, you must use .byte and the respective byte value.
; Bytes that change text color will change the color of everything
; that is written after it, until another color is used.

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "Dont ever do that"
.byte 0x0A ;
.ascii "again you freak"
.byte 0xC2 ;
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
; .byte 0x5C ; Apostrophe (')
; .byte 0x29 ; Coin icon
; .byte 0x3D ; - (minus)
; .byte 0x3E ; x (multiply)
; .byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

; If your message has an image, use this at the start of each line
; .byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Padding for picture

.align 4
PlaySadVoice:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP 

LUI T1 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Character address
MULT V0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by T0
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to T0

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's Character address
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into T0

ADDIU V0 T0 0x287 ; Mario's Sad Voice Index

MOVE A0 V0 ; Pass the Voice Index to A0

; NAME: Red Space Ruleset

;====================================================================
; Made by Spongyoshi, feel free to use for your own boards!!
; Part of the last five turns custom event, put it on every red space
; Will trigger either battle, bowser, game guy, chance time or red
; Thanks to Rain and the Mario Party Legacy Discord as always!!
;===================================================================
;TESTING BEGIN;
LUI S3 hi(0x800CD0A1)
ADDIU S3 S3 lo(0x800CD0A1) ; Loading ram address
LBU S3 0(S3)
LI S2 2
BEQ S3 S2 Start ; If rule 2 is active then begin
NOP
J exit ;else, exit
NOP
;TESTING END;
;SOUNDEFFECT BEGIN;
Start:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x143 ;Shinning Star
JAL SleepProcess
ADDIU A0 R0 60 ;Sleep for 60 frames for anticipation
;SOUNDEFFECT END;
;RANDOM BEGIN;
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 64 ; Is the number less than 64?
BNE S0 R0 DetermineIfBowser
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 128 ; Is the number less than 128?
BNE S0 R0 DetermineIfBattle
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 192 ; Is the number less than 192?
BNE S0 R0 DetermineIfGameGuy
NOP
J DetermineIfChanceTime
NOP
;RANDOM END;
;CONDITION BEGIN;
DetermineIfBowser:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 200 ; Is the number less than 200?
BNE S0 R0 BowserTransformation
NOP
J RedSpaceTransformation
NOP
DetermineIfBattle:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 200 ; Is the number less than 200?
BNE S0 R0 BattleTransformation
NOP
J RedSpaceTransformation
NOP
DetermineIfGameGuy:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 200 ; Is the number less than 200?
BNE S0 R0 GameGuyTransformation
NOP
J RedSpaceTransformation
NOP
DetermineIfChanceTime:
JAL GetRandomByte ; Random Int at V0
NOP
SLTI S0 V0 200 ; Is the number less than 200?
BNE S0 R0 ChanceTimeTransformation
NOP
J RedSpaceTransformation
NOP
;CONDITION END;
;SPACE CHANGE BEGIN;
BowserTransformation:
JAL GetCurrentSpaceIndex
NOP
MOVE A0 V0 
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 0x0C
J exit
NOP
BattleTransformation:
JAL GetCurrentSpaceIndex
NOP
MOVE A0 V0 
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 0x09
J exit
NOP
GameGuyTransformation:
JAL GetCurrentSpaceIndex
NOP
MOVE A0 V0 
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 0x0F
J exit
NOP
ChanceTimeTransformation:
JAL GetCurrentSpaceIndex
NOP
MOVE A0 V0 
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 0x05
J exit
NOP
RedSpaceTransformation:
JAL GetCurrentSpaceIndex
NOP
MOVE A0 V0 
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 0x02
;SPACE CHANGE END;

NOP

NOP

Black Hole Warp FIXED (Boardwalk).code:
; NAME: Black Hole Warp FIXED (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 8 ; Fade Out for 8 Frames

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_6

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 6 ; Sleep 6 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)
;WARP END------------------------------------------------------------

;SOUND START---------------------------------------------------------
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 10 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 10 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 10 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 10 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x257 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 9 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 20 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish
;SOUND END-----------------------------------------------------------

;FADE-IN START-------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 4 ; Happening Space Fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames of Fade-in

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 31 ; Sleep for 31 Frames
;FADE-IN END---------------------------------------------------------

;MESSAGE DISPLAY START-----------------------------------------------
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0x0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL CloseMessage
NOP
;MESSAGE DISPLAY END-------------------------------------------------



LW RA 76(SP)
LW S4 72(SP)
LW S5 68(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; .ascii is used to output Text. Anything surrounded by " will be 
; displayed in the message (Special characters are not included).
; For those, you must use .byte and the respective byte value.
; Bytes that change text color will change the color of everything
; that is written after it, until another color is used.

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "You were saved by Big Boo"
.byte 0xC2 ; 
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
; .byte 0x5C ; Apostrophe (')
; .byte 0x29 ; Coin icon
; .byte 0x3D ; - (minus)
; .byte 0x3E ; x (multiply)
; .byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

; If your message has an image, use this at the start of each line
; .byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Padding for picture

.align 4
PlaySadVoice:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP 

LUI T1 hi(p1_char)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(p1_char) ; Load Player 1's Character address
LI T0 0x38 ; Distance between each player's Character address
MULT V0 T0 ;  Multiply Current Player Index by T0
MFLO T0 ; Move the result to T0

ADDU T1 T1 T0 ; Add result to get current Player's Character address
LBU T0 0(T1) ; Load address value into T0

ADDIU V0 T0 0x287 ; Mario's Sad Voice Index

JAL PlaySound
MOVE A0 V0 ; Pass the Voice Index to A0

LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

ADDIU SP SP -104

ADDIU A0 A0 12

NOP

LI A0 0x257 ;

ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

LI T2 0x38 ; Distance between each player's addresses

; NAME: Black Hole Warp FIXED FINAL (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 12 ; Boo Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 8 ; Fade Out for 8 Frames

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_6

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 6 ; Sleep 6 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)
;WARP END------------------------------------------------------------

;SOUND START---------------------------------------------------------
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr
JAL PlaySound 
LI A0 0x153 ; Warp Block Sound Index

JAL SleepProcess 
LI A0 8 ; Number of frames the game waits for sound to finish

;MESSAGE DISPLAY START-----------------------------------------------
SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0x0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0x0

JAL CloseMessage
NOP
;MESSAGE DISPLAY END-------------------------------------------------



LW RA 76(SP)
LW S4 72(SP)
LW S5 68(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

; .ascii is used to output Text. Anything surrounded by " will be 
; displayed in the message (Special characters are not included).
; For those, you must use .byte and the respective byte value.
; Bytes that change text color will change the color of everything
; that is written after it, until another color is used.

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "You were saved by Big Boo"
.byte 0xC2 ; 
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)

Black Hole Warp FIXED FINAL BETTER (Boar.code:
; NAME: Black Hole Warp FIXED FINAL BETTER (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PreviousSpace
; PARAM: Space|NextSpace

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is specifically designed to warp a player who
;            lands on a Space into a Space of the same type.
;            This is due to limitations on how warps execute.
;
;            Destination is where the player will warp to.
;            PreviousSpace is the space the player will step into if
;            they go in reverse after the warp.
;            NextSpace is the next space that the player will step
;            into if they roll normally.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S4 72(SP) ; Current Player's Index
SW S5 68(SP) ; Current Player's Struct

;FADE-OUT START------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 12 ; Boo Space Fade-out 
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 8 ; Fade Out for 8 Frames

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_6

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 6 ; Sleep 6 Frames
;FADE-OUT END--------------------------------------------------------

JAL PlaySadVoice ; Plays Current Player Character's Scream
NOP

JAL SleepVProcess
NOP

;WARP START----------------------------------------------------------
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Current Player's Index to S4

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 Destination_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LI A2 Destination_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 PreviousSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LI A2 PreviousSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
LI A1 NextSpace_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LI A2 NextSpace_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S5 V0

LI A0 Destination_chain_index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LI A1 Destination_chain_space_index

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE T0 V1 ; Copy to T0

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F0 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F1 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 T1 F0 ; Move total to T1?

LW V1 0x24(S5) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW T1 0(V1)

Big Boo Hootenanny + (EX) [Airsolaâ„¢] (.code:
; NAME: Big Boo Hootenanny + (EX) [Airsolaâ„¢] (Boardwalk)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|WhichHootenanny
; PARAM: +Number|Price1
; PARAM: +Number|Price2
; PARAM: Space|BeforeHootenanny
; PARAM: Space|AfterHootenanny
; PARAM: Space|BeforeHootenanny2x

;====================================================================
; IMPORTANT: This code is designed to replicate the Hootenanny event 
;            from Mario Party 2... and more!
;
;			 If the WhichHootenanny parameter is set to 0 it's 
;            going to offer the Vanilla Hootenanny, if it's 1, it's 
;            the EX version, which also poisons the other players and 
;            extends your roll by 3, and if it's set to 2, the player
;            will be able to select between both Vanilla and EX.
;			 
;			 If you're only allowing the use of 1 of the Hootenannys,
;			 then Price1 is the parameter for how much it would cost.
;			 
;            If you're allowing the player to select between both of
;            them, then Price1 is the price of Vanilla, and Price2 is 
;            the price of EX. (PRICE2 SHOULD NEVER BE LOWER!!!)
;            
;            BeforeHootenanny is the Space before the event's location.
;            AfterHootenanny is the Space after the event's location.
;			 BeforeHootenanny2x is the Space before BeforeHootenanny.
;
;            This event is made as a passing event, and is not
;            expected to work as a landing event. 
;			 
;			 At the bottom of the code you will find useful links and
;			 explanations for some technical things in the code.
;====================================================================

ADDIU SP SP -120
SW RA 116(SP)
SW S0 112(SP) ; Option chosen / Loop Counter
SW S1 108(SP) ; Float holder for position changes
SW S2 104(SP) ; Unused
SW S3 100(SP) ; Unused
SW S4 96(SP) ; Current Player Struct
SW S5 92(SP) ; Destination Array
SW S6 88(SP) ; Price
SW S7 84(SP) ; Hootenanny Index (0 for Vanilla, 1 for EX)



JAL RefreshOptionArray ; Resets the Array colors 
NOP

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 -1 ; Idle Animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation 
LI A3 2 ; Loop

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
MOVE S4 V0 ; Copy Struct to S4

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL PlayerHasCoins ; V0 = 1 if they have enough, 0 if not 
LI A1 Price1 ; Cost for the event

BNEZ V0 determineprompt ; If they have the coins necessary, continue
NOP

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x25E ; Boo cry (Sad?)

LUI A1 hi(NotEnoughCoins_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(NotEnoughCoins_Message)

J exit
NOP 

determineprompt:
LI T1 2 ; Index for Prompt using both Hootenannys
LI T0 WhichHootenanny 
BEQ T0 T1 doublehootenannyprompt ; Branch if it's both in 1 prompt
NOP

MOVE S7 T0 ; Move Hootenanny index to S7

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Boo cry (Happy?)

LUI A0 hi(Price1_Pointer)
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(Price1_Pointer) ; Parse Destination
LUI A1 hi(percent_d)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(percent_d) ; String Format
JAL sprintf
LI A2 Price1 ; Convert Price into string

LBU A2 3(S4) ; Current Player Character Index
LUI A3 hi(Price1_Pointer)
ADDIU A3 A3 lo(Price1_Pointer)

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 7 ; Character image (Boo)
LUI A1 hi(Hootenanny_Prompt)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Hootenanny_Prompt)
ADDIU A2 A2 0x1C00 ; Add to get Character Name
JAL ShowMessage
NOP

JAL RNGPercentChance ; 0 or 1 at V0
LI A0 50 ; 50% Chance Yes/No

LI A0 2 ; Pick whatever is in A1 as AI's Choice
JAL GetBasicPromptSelection
MOVE A1 V0 ; Say Yes or No
MOVE S0 V0 ; Chosen Option Index

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage ; 3 Functions to close the message properly
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LI T0 1 ; Second option index
BEQ S0 T0 declined
NOP
LI T0 2 ; Third option index
BEQ S0 T0 viewmap
NOP

LI S6 Price1
doublehootenannyjump:
LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
SUBU A1 R0 S6

LBU A0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
SUBU A1 R0 S6

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Frames

LUI A1 hi(CallingEveryone_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CallingEveryone_Message)

LI A0 1 ; Circle Fade
JAL InitFade
LI A1 0 ; Fade type (Out)

LUI S5 hi(DestinationSpaces_Array)
ADDIU S5 S5 lo(DestinationSpaces_Array)

JAL GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex ; Chain Index on V0, Chain Space Index on V1
LI A0 BeforeHootenanny
SB V0 0(S5) ; Store Destination Chain Index
SB V1 1(S5) ; Store Destination Chain Space Index

JAL GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex ; Chain Index on V0, Chain Space Index on V1
LI A0 AfterHootenanny
SB V0 2(S5) ; Store NextSpace Chain Index
SB V1 3(S5) ; Store NextSpace Chain Space Index

JAL GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex ; Chain Index on V0, Chain Space Index on V1
LI A0 BeforeHootenanny2x
SB V0 4(S5) ; Store PreviousSpace Chain Index
SB V1 5(S5) ; Store PreviousSpace Chain Space Index

LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 4
LI S1 0xC1200000 ; -10 (Float) for X pos
hootenannyloop:
BLTZ S0 hootenannyloop_exit
NOP
LBU T0 29(S4) ; Current Player's Index
BEQL S0 T0 hootenannyloop ; Loop if this is the turn player
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player

MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index
MOVE A1 S5 ; Space Array Pointer
JAL SetPlayerOntoChainVisually
MOVE A2 S1 ; Float for X pos

LI T0 0x41200000 ; 10 (Float) 
MTC1 S1 F0 ; X pos adjustment to F0
MTC1 T0 F1 ; 5 to F1
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add 5 to scoot next player to the right
MFC1 S1 F0 ; Return float to S1

BEQL S7 R0 hootenannyloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Struct at V0
MOVE A0 S0 ; Player Index

LUI T3 hi(0x800CD0AF)
ADDIU T3 T3 lo(0x800CD0AF) ; Cursed Dice Flag Address
LBU T4 0(T3) ; Flag Value
MOVE T2 S0 ; This player's Index
LI T5 1 
SLLV T6 T5 T2 ; Shift left by player's index
AND T1 T4 T6 ; Compare Flag Value to Player Index
; V0 returns 0 if not Curse is not active, 1 if it is.
BNEZL T1 hootenannyloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player

LI T5 1
SLLV T5 T5 T2 ; Shift by the player's index
ADDU T4 T4 T5 ; Add to current flag value
SB T4 0(T3)

LI T0 2 ; Poison Mushroom png 
LBU T1 23(V0) ; This player's Status Flags
ADDU T1 T0 T1 ; Add Poison Mushroom png
SB T1 23(V0) ; This player's Status Flags

J hootenannyloop
ADDIU S0 S0 -1 ; Subtract 1 to get next player

hootenannyloop_exit:
LI A0 1 ; Circle Fade
JAL InitFade
LI A1 1 ; Fade type (In)

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x257 ; Boo cry (Happy?)

LUI A1 hi(EveryoneReady_Message)
JAL ShowMessage_Function
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(EveryoneReady_Message)

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 0x4A ; Sound Config

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 6 ; Star Get Animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2 ; Loop

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 90 ; Frames

LI A0 1 ; Circle Fadeout
JAL InitFade
LI A1 0 ; Fade Type (Out)

BEQZ S7 skipthegoodstuff ; If it's a regular Hootenanny, skip to the end
NOP

LUI T0 hi(cur_player_spaces_remaining)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(cur_player_spaces_remaining) ; Address on T0
LW T1 0(T0) 
ADDIU T1 T1 3 ; Add 3 to player's remaining roll
SW T1 0(T0)

LUI T3 hi(0x800CDBD2)
ADDIU T3 T3 lo(0x800CDBD2) ; P1 Forced Roll Address

LI T2 0x4C ; Distance between each player's addresses
LBU T4 29(S4) ; Player Index
MULT T4 T2 ; Multiply Current Player Index by T2
MFLO T2 ; Move Result to T2
ADDU T3 T3 T2 ; Add to get current Player's Forced Roll address
SB T1 3(T3) ; Store new remaining roll

LI S0 3 ; Start with Player 3
soundloop:
BLTZ S0 soundloop_exit
NOP

BEQL S0 T0 soundloop

RefreshOptionArray:
ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)

LUI T0 hi(OptionColoring_StaticArray)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(OptionColoring_StaticArray)
LUI T2 hi(OptionColoring_Array)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(OptionColoring_Array)
LI T3 0xFF ; Nothing left to refresh
RefreshOptionArray_loop:
LBU T1 0(T0) ; Load first value to refresh array
BEQ T1 T3 RefreshOptionArray_exit ; Leave once it reaches 0xFF
NOP
SB T1 0(T2) ; Store first value to refresh
ADDIU T0 T0 1 ; add 1 to get next value
ADDIU T2 T2 1 ; add 1 to get next value
J RefreshOptionArray_loop
NOP

RefreshOptionArray_exit:
LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA 
ADDIU SP SP 40

SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6

JAL 0x800EC6EC

NOP

LW RA 76(SP)

.align 16
GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex:
//takes arg a0, abs_space_index
//returns chain_index to v0
//returns space_index to v1
ADDIU sp, sp, -0x40 
SW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
SW s0, 0x001C (sp)
SW s1, 0x0020 (sp)
SW s2, 0x0024 (sp)
SW s3, 0x0028 (sp)
SW s4, 0x002C (sp)
SW s5, 0x0030 (sp)
SW s6, 0x0034 (sp)
ORI s3, r0, 0x0000 //init s3 to 0
ADDIU s4, r0, 0xFFFF //init s4 to FFFF, loop1 counter
LUI s0, 0x8010
LW s0, 0x5218 (s0) //load ptr to beginning of hydrated chains ptr
DADDU s1, a0, r0 ;move abs_space_index to s0
Loop:
ADDIU s4, s4, 0x0001 //add 1 to current loop total
LHU s2, 0x0000 (s0) //load total number of space_indicies in chain
BEQ s2, r0, error
NOP
ORI t0, r0, 0x0000 //going to be used for loop 2 counter
LW s3, 0x0004 (s0) //load pointer that points to abs space_indicies for current chain in loop
Loop2:
//
LHU t1, 0x0000 (s3) //load abs value from hydrated chain
BEQ t1, s1, isabs
NOP
ADDIU t0, t0, 0x0001 //add 1 to loop2 counter
BEQ t0, s2, backtoLoop1
NOP
BEQ r0, r0, Loop2
ADDIU s3, s3, 0x0002
returnvalues:
//
GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex_exit:
LW ra, 0x0018 (sp)
LW s0, 0x001C (sp)
LW s1, 0x0020 (sp)
LW s2, 0x0024 (sp)
LW s3, 0x0028 (sp)
LW s4, 0x002C (sp)
LW s5, 0x0030 (sp)
LW s6, 0x0034 (sp)
JR RA
ADDIU sp, sp, 0x40
error:
ORI v0, r0, 0xFFFF //error, return FFFF
BEQ r0, r0, GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex_exit
ORI v1, r0, 0xFFFF //error, return FFFF
isabs:
//s4 holds current chain index
//t1 holds current space index in chain
ADD v0, s4, r0 //move chain index to v0
BEQ r0, r0, GetChainAndSpaceIndexFromAbsSpaceIndex_exit
ADD v1, t0, r0 //move space_index to v1
backtoLoop1:
BEQ r0, r0, Loop
ADDIU s0, s0, 0x0008 //advance to next hydrated chains ptr

.align 16
SetPlayerOntoChainVisually:
ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S0 72(SP) ; Array Pointer
SB A0 68(SP) ; Player's Index 
SW A2 56(SP) ; Float to adjust X pos

MOVE S0 A1 ; Copy Array Pointer to S0

BNEZ S7 SetPlayerOntoChainVisuallyEX 
NOP

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 0(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LBU A2 1(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 15(S4) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LBU A2 16(S4) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 4(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LBU A2 5(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2
J visualwarp
NOP

SetPlayerOntoChainVisuallyEX:
LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 15(S4) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
LBU A2 16(S4) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 2(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
LBU A2 3(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LBU A0 68(SP) ; Player Index
LBU A1 0(S0) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
LBU A2 1(S0) ; Assigns Space Index to A2


visualwarp:
LBU A0 15(S4) ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; Gets True Space Index at V0
LBU A1 16(S4) ; Assigns Space Index to A2

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 V0 ; True Space Index

LW T0 56(SP) ; X pos adjustment float to T0
LW V1 8(V0) ; Space X pos
MTC1 V1 F0 ; Space X pos to F0
MTC1 T0 F1 ; X pos adjustment float to F1
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add/Subtract X pos adjustment
MFC1 V1 F0 ; Copy value to V1
SW V1 64(SP) ; Store on the Stack

LI T0 0x41200000 ; Y pos adjustment
LW V1 16(V0) ; Space Y pos
MTC1 V1 F0 ; Space Y pos to F0
MTC1 T0 F1 ; Y pos adjustment float to F1
ADD.S F0 F0 F1 ; Add Y pos adjustment
MFC1 V1 F0 ; Copy value to V1
SW V1 60(SP) ; Store on the Stack

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LBU A0 68(SP)  ; Player Index

LW V1 0x24(V0) ; Load Offset 0x24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
LW T0 64(SP) ; Load Space X Coords from Stack
SW T0 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
LW T1 60(SP) ; Load Space Y Coords from Stack
SW T1 0(V1)

LW S0 72(SP) ; Array Pointer
LW RA 76(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

.align 16
GetColorFormatter:
ADDIU SP SP -60
SW RA 56(SP)

LUI V0 hi(BlackColor_ptr)
ADDIU V0 V0 lo(BlackColor_ptr) ; First Option (Hootenanny EX)
LUI T7 hi(OptionColoring_Array)
ADDIU T7 T7 lo(OptionColoring_Array) ; Array for disabling options

LI T8 8 ; White Color

LI T0 Price2
LHU T1 10(S4) ; Current Player's Coins

SLT T6 T1 T0 ; ON IF not enough Coins for Hootenanny EX
BNEZ T6 GetColorFormatter_exit ; exit if not enough Coins 
NOP

LUI V0 hi(WhiteColor_ptr) ; White Color
ADDIU V0 V0 lo(WhiteColor_ptr)
SB T8 1(T7) ; Don't disable 2nd Option (Hootenanny EX)


GetColorFormatter_exit:
LW RA 56(SP)
JR RA 
ADDIU SP SP 60

.align 16
DisableOptions:
ADDIU SP SP -72
SW RA 68(SP)
SW A0 64(SP) ; Window ID
SW FP 60(SP) ; Address of Option Disable Array


LUI FP hi(OptionColoring_Array)
ADDIU FP FP lo(OptionColoring_Array) ; Array of answers to disable
loadbyte:
LBU T0 0(FP) ; Load Byte of Array
LI T1 0xFF
BEQ T0 T1 DisableOptions_exit ; Exit once array is fully checked
NOP
LI T1 8 ; Index to not disable
BEQL T0 T1 loadbyte
ADDIU FP FP 1 ; Load next Byte

LW A0 64(SP) ; Window ID?
JAL DisablePromptOption
MOVE A1 T0 ; Disable First Option

J loadbyte
ADDIU FP FP 1


DisableOptions_exit:
LW FP 60(SP)
LW A0 64(SP)
LW RA 68(SP)
JR RA 
ADDIU SP SP 72

GetAISelection:
ADDIU SP SP -80
SW RA 76(SP)

GetAISelectionreroll:
JAL GetRandomByte ; 0-255 at V0
NOP
LI T0 3 ; 3 Choices
DIVU V0 T0 ; Divide by 3
MFHI V0 ; Remainder to V0 (0-2)

LUI T0 hi(OptionColoring_Array)
ADDIU T0 T0 lo(OptionColoring_Array)
ADDU T0 T0 V0 ; Add the number to get correct array index
LBU T1 0(T0) ; Load color of that option

LI T2 1 ; Black color, option is grayed out
BEQ T1 T2 GetAISelectionreroll ; Reroll if that option isn't available
NOP

LW RA 76(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

boardevents.id: Last 5 Turns Event (Boardwalk Version) [NO BANK-NO BOOST]

audioData.name: The Adventure Halts (The Adventure Begins NH SB20).mid

audioSelectCode.code:
; Customize the background music used each turn!
; This function runs whenever the board music starts playing.
; Custom tracks you've added are available as MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_#,
; e.g. MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_1 for the first added custom song.
; (If you aren't using custom music, then only MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_1
; exists and it is set to the in-game music index you chose.)
LI t0, 0x800CD05A
LBU t1, 0 (t0) ;total turns
LBU t2, 1, (t0) ;current turn
SUBU t1, t1, t2 ; maxTurn - currentTurn
SLTI t0, t1, 5
BEQZ t0, normalMusic
NOP

LI V0 MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_2
BEQ r0, r0, end
NOP

normalMusic:
LI V0 MUSIC_TRACK_INDEX_1
BEQ r0, r0, end
NOP

end:
JR RA
NOP
